    {
      "id": 579,
      "from_id": "cec50b17:20",
      "to_id": "cec50b17:0",
      "content": "DONE — Revised fix complete. Build clean.\n\n**Root cause of \"Developer :21\" in settings.json (confirmed):**\n\nBefore ff6d5e3, `update_status` accepted a `name` parameter and called `saveSettings({ name: newName })` when it changed. A worker passed `name=\"Developer :21\"` at some point, persisting it to disk. ff6d5e3 removed that code path but left the stale value in the file. The commit at ff6d5e3 also introduced `let agentName = settings.name ?? ''` which then re-read the stale value on every boot and propagated it back to the DB on every `update_status` call — creating the regression.\n\n**What was written by the pre-ff6d5e3 code:**\n```ts\n// OLD (removed in ff6d5e3):\nif (newName && newName !== agentName) {\n  agentName = newName;\n  saveSettings({ name: newName });  // ← wrote \"Developer :21\" to settings.json\n}\n```\n\n**Files changed (in commit 6fced86, auto-committed by hook):**\n- `src/mcp-server.ts`: removed `agentName` variable + old slot-0 guard; simplified to `if (slot === 0) { setAgentName(AGENT_ID, 'orchestrator'); }`; `update_status` handler passes `null` for name; dropped dead `saveSettings()` and `name?` from `Settings` interface\n- `src/db.ts`: migration WHERE extended to `name = 'Joker' OR name LIKE 'Developer :%'`\n\n**`.synapse/settings.json` final contents (gitignored, updated on disk):**\n```json\n{\n  \"projectId\": \"cec50b17\",\n  \"name\": \"synapse\"\n}\n```\nRestored `name` to project dir basename `\"synapse\"` per option (a).\n\n**Build:** clean, no errors.\n\n**Note:** The slot-0 guard now calls `setAgentName(AGENT_ID, 'orchestrator')` unconditionally on every boot. If operator-customized orchestrator names should survive restarts, add a DB read before the call to skip if a non-default name is already set. Let me know if you want that added.\n",
      "priority": 5,
      "created_at": 1780674208318,
      "read_at": 1780674220786,
